{"rows": [{"updated": "2018-04-19T19:32:26.626433+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader", "selector": [{"conformsTo": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3236", "type": "FragmentSelector", "value": "sec5"}, {"endContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[5]/p[2]", "startContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[5]/p[2]", "type": "RangeSelector", "startOffset": 45, "endOffset": 177}, {"type": "TextPositionSelector", "end": 97680, "start": 97548}, {"exact": "In 1951, there were two white\ninmates for each minority inmate. By 2011, prisons held three minority inmates for\neach white inmate. ", "prefix": "er men's prisons in California. ", "type": "TextQuoteSelector", "suffix": "This represents a radical shift "}]}], "links": {"json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/GFmB1AK_Eeio9O8RHp3yNQ", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/GFmB1AK_Eeio9O8RHp3yNQ", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/GFmB1AK_Eeio9O8RHp3yNQ/www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader"}, "tags": [], "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic note:** I collected the data on California ethnic fractionalization from annual reports released by the California Department of Corrections and Rehabilitation. \n\n**Full Citation:** California Department of Corrections and Rehabilitation. 2012. Prison Census Data. Data Analysis Unit.", "created": "2018-01-26T17:34:00.280641+00:00", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader", "flagged": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}, "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "hidden": false, "document": {"title": ["Covenants without the Sword? Comparing Prison Self-Governance\n                        Globally"]}, "id": "GFmB1AK_Eeio9O8RHp3yNQ", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}}, {"updated": "2018-04-19T19:31:50.358294+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader", "selector": [{"conformsTo": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3236", "type": "FragmentSelector", "value": "sec3-1"}, {"endContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[21]", "startContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[21]", "type": "RangeSelector", "startOffset": 601, "endOffset": 682}, {"type": "TextPositionSelector", "end": 68631, "start": 68550}, {"exact": "The better the\ngovernance institutions, the more the home is worth on the market.", "prefix": "hat govern the housing section. ", "type": "TextQuoteSelector", "suffix": " The presence\nof different housi"}]}], "links": {"json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/typ_YgK-EeibkOdbmgJNJQ", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/typ_YgK-EeibkOdbmgJNJQ", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/typ_YgK-EeibkOdbmgJNJQ/www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader"}, "tags": [], "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic note:** This seems to be true, based on resident's observations. However, there is no strong, quantitative evidence to establish this relationship. Given the way in which prisoners describe the market, it seems reasonable that prices would reflect quality.\n\n**Full Citation:** Stringham, E. 2015. Private Governance: Creating Order in Economic and Social Life. New York: Oxford University Press.\n\nTiebout, C. M. 1956. \u201cA Pure Theory of Local Expenditures.\u201d The Journal of Political Economy, 416\u201324.", "created": "2018-01-26T17:31:17.266788+00:00", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader", "flagged": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}, "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "hidden": false, "document": {"title": ["Covenants without the Sword? Comparing Prison Self-Governance\n                        Globally"]}, "id": "typ_YgK-EeibkOdbmgJNJQ", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}}, {"updated": "2018-04-19T19:30:03.637581+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader", "selector": [{"conformsTo": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3236", "type": "FragmentSelector", "value": "sec3-1"}, {"endContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[11]", "startContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[11]", "type": "RangeSelector", "startOffset": 165, "endOffset": 251}, {"type": "TextPositionSelector", "end": 61420, "start": 61334}, {"exact": "Guards restrict access to\nthe facility and prevent escape, but do almost nothing else.", "prefix": "ernance exists (Skarbek\n2010b). ", "type": "TextQuoteSelector", "suffix": " Officials provide\nno rehabilita"}]}], "links": {"json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/2r1szgK9EeiiVB9DKWbSag", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/2r1szgK9EeiiVB9DKWbSag", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/2r1szgK9EeiiVB9DKWbSag/www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader"}, "tags": [], "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic note:** The claim that officials provide little to no governance is surprising, and one that I initially met with skepticism. However, the number of confirming accounts, from a wide range of source (cited here, but also a large literature), provide confidence in the claim. More generally, as one observes the shockingly low quality of official governance in many Latin American prisons, the case in Bolivia becomes less unusual and more plausible.\n\n**Full Citations:** Baltimore, B., A. Bastien van der Meer, M. Brennan, M. Burton, M. Castillo, L. Cavise, A. Davis, J. Friedman-Rudovsky, A. Mendoza, D. Oliveira, J. Somberg,V. Spinazola, K. Staskawicz, L. Stern, and L. Tockman, et al. 2007. Report of Delegation to Bolivia. New York: National Lawyers Guild.\n\nOrganization of American States. 2007. Access to Justice and Social Inclusion: The Road Towards Strengthening Democracy in Bolivia. Washington, DC: Inter-American Commission on Human Rights.", "created": "2018-01-26T17:25:07.388542+00:00", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader", "flagged": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}, "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "hidden": false, "document": {"title": ["Covenants without the Sword? Comparing Prison Self-Governance\n                        Globally"]}, "id": "2r1szgK9EeiiVB9DKWbSag", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}}, {"updated": "2018-04-19T19:29:05.250465+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader", "selector": [{"conformsTo": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3236", "type": "FragmentSelector", "value": "sec3-1"}, {"endContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[4]", "startContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[4]", "type": "RangeSelector", "startOffset": 935, "endOffset": 996}, {"type": "TextPositionSelector", "end": 57756, "start": 57695}, {"exact": "and their use has coincided with a dramatic fall in\nviolence ", "prefix": " courts to\nadjudicate disputes, ", "type": "TextQuoteSelector", "suffix": "(Denyer Willis 2015,\n60\u20133; Dias "}]}], "links": {"json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/bJdxqgK8EeiV0bPL9X2TDQ", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/bJdxqgK8EeiV0bPL9X2TDQ", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/bJdxqgK8EeiV0bPL9X2TDQ/www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader"}, "tags": [], "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic note:** While it is difficult to establish a precise causal relationship between these factors, there is a substantial amount of supportive evidence. The authors cited have a deep knowledge of crime and prisons in Brazil. They provide credible information about the existence and operation of the gang's adjudication procedures and credible data on prison violence. Of course, there may be endogeneity problems or confounding variables, but given the rich qualitative evidence available, the causal relationship seems highly likely. \n\n**Full Citations:** Denyer Willis, G. 2015. The Killing Consensus: Police, Organized\nCrime, and the Regulation of Life and Death in Urban Brazil. Berkeley: University of California Press.\n\nDias,C. N., and F. Salla. 2013. \u201cOrganized Crime in Brazilian Prisons:\nThe Example of the PCC.\u201d International Journal of Criminology and Sociology 2: 397\u2013408.", "created": "2018-01-26T17:14:53.153537+00:00", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader", "flagged": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}, "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "hidden": false, "document": {"title": ["Covenants without the Sword? Comparing Prison Self-Governance\n                        Globally"]}, "id": "bJdxqgK8EeiV0bPL9X2TDQ", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}}, {"updated": "2018-04-19T19:28:16.339117+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader", "selector": [{"conformsTo": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3236", "type": "FragmentSelector", "value": "sec3-1"}, {"endContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[4]", "startContainer": "/section[5]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[1]/div[3]/div[1]/p[4]", "type": "RangeSelector", "startOffset": 268, "endOffset": 324}, {"type": "TextPositionSelector", "end": 57084, "start": 57028}, {"exact": "from the ordinary moments to the\nmost exceptional ones\u201d ", "prefix": "mprehend the day-to-day events, ", "type": "TextQuoteSelector", "suffix": "(Varella 1999, 109). They played"}]}], "links": {"json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/-Y1soAK7Eeij54eS1h3Hjg", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/-Y1soAK7Eeij54eS1h3Hjg", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/-Y1soAK7Eeij54eS1h3Hjg/www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader"}, "tags": [], "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic note:** This quote is representative of other accounts, and I used it because the author was in the best place possible to make this assessment. He worked in the prison for a long period in a context that would allow for informal and open conversations with prisoners and observations of their activity.\n\n**Full Citation:** Varella, D. 1999. Lockdown: Inside Brazil\u2019s Most Dangerous Prison. London: Simon & Schuster.", "created": "2018-01-26T17:11:40.073576+00:00", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader", "flagged": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}, "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "hidden": false, "document": {"title": ["Covenants without the Sword? Comparing Prison Self-Governance\n                        Globally"]}, "id": "-Y1soAK7Eeij54eS1h3Hjg", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}}, {"updated": "2018-04-18T18:28:05.018614+00:00", "group": "zvEVDE2R", "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader", "selector": [{"endContainer": "/section[4]/div[1]/div[1]/h1[1]", "startContainer": "/section[4]/div[1]/div[1]/h1[1]", "type": "RangeSelector", "startOffset": 0, "endOffset": 70}, {"type": "TextPositionSelector", "end": 1944, "start": 1874}, {"exact": "Covenants without the Sword? Comparing Prison Self-Governance\nGlobally", "prefix": "t;\n              }\n            \n", "type": "TextQuoteSelector", "suffix": "\n\n\n\n\n\n    var coreReaderAccess ="}]}], "links": {"json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/-jw5lAK5EeiZActvB2RE-Q", "html": "https://hypothes.is/a/-jw5lAK5EeiZActvB2RE-Q", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/-jw5lAK5EeiZActvB2RE-Q/www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader"}, "tags": [], "text": "<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\nThis is an Annotation for Transparent Inquiry project, published by the <a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu\">Qualitative Data Repository</a>.\n\n<br/>\n\n<strong><font>The <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.5064/F6AGINR7\">Data Overview</a> discusses project context, data generation and analysis, and logic of annotation.</font></strong>\n\n<br/>\nPlease cite as:\n\nSkarbek, David. 2018. \"Data for: Covenants without the sword? Comparing prison self-governance globally\". Qualitative Data Repository. https://doi.org/10.5064/F6AGINR7\n\nLearn more about ATI <a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/ati\">here</a>.\n", "created": "2018-01-26T16:57:22.203332+00:00", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/american-political-science-review/article/covenants-without-the-sword-comparing-prison-selfgovernance-globally/8B6C1317700957B3981527B42A8360C0/core-reader", "flagged": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}, "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "hidden": false, "document": {"title": ["Covenants without the Sword? Comparing Prison Self-Governance\n                        Globally"]}, "id": "-jw5lAK5EeiZActvB2RE-Q", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}}], "total": 6}